  <h1>Settings</h1>
  <p class="lead">Make Pandia yours.</p>

  <h2>What you can set</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Theme</strong> — any of the built-in dark and light themes, or Auto.</li>
    <li><strong>Density</strong> — compact, normal, or comfortable.</li>
    <li><strong>Code font &amp; size</strong> — pick your monospace font and adjust its size.</li>
    <li><strong>Sidebar panels</strong> — choose which panels are enabled, and which side the
    sidebar docks.</li>
    <li><strong>Behaviour preferences</strong> — tune how Pandia behaves day to day.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>For everything visual — themes, fonts, density and syntax colours — see
  <a href="/docs/themes">Themes &amp; appearance</a>.</p>

  <h2>Auto-save &amp; recovery</h2>
  <p>Pandia keeps <strong>crash-recovery backups</strong> as you work. If it closes unexpectedly,
  the next launch offers to restore your unsaved work. You can also turn on
  <strong>auto-save on idle</strong> in Behaviour settings to write file-backed documents to disk
  after a short pause.</p>
  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>Note —</strong> recovery is automatic. You don't have to enable anything; if there's
    unsaved work after an unexpected close, Pandia surfaces it for you to restore. Auto-save on idle
    is off by default — turn it on if you want it.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Export your settings</h2>
  <p>Your settings can be <strong>exported as a JSON bundle</strong> — handy for backing them up or
  carrying your setup to another machine.</p>
</DocsLayout>
